content:
CRM Analytics and Salesforce Data Pipelines Work Together

These products are unique but share settings, limits, and assets when used together. Features shared include:

* Limits: Some unique, some shared, some pooled.
* Datasets: Shared, with inheritance and security predicates supported for Data Pipelines-generated datasets used in CRM Analytics.
* Input and Output Connections: Shared, built for one product can be used in the other.
* Synced Data: Shared, input, output, and synced out data from one product can be used in the other.
* Recipes: Unique, but can be reassigned to the other product.

Use either product's limits when building recipes. Select which product's limits you want a recipe's run and dataset to use. Use either product's datasets as inputs to avoid recreating and updating recipes in both products.

To use data from a CRM Analytics or Data Pipeline recipe in the other product, add the dataset as an input node and reassign the license on the recipe as needed. Manage and track the product associated with recipes and datasets on the Data Manager.

Datasets generated by one product can be used in the other, but users with only one license type don't see the other license type's datasets.
title: Integrating CRM Analytics with Salesforce Data Pipelines
